12.41	Spanish_language_in_the_Philippines	Spanish language in the Philippines	Spanish (as Castilian or "Philippine Spanish" (español filipino) was imposed as an official language of the Philippines from the beginning of Spanish rule since the times of Miguel López de Legazpi in the late 16th century, through American rule and independence, until the change of Constitution in 1973. Spanish was then redesignated an official language by Presidential decree, and remained official until a subsequent change in constitution in 1987 removed its official status.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Lopez_de_Legazpi.jpg/190px-Lopez_de_Legazpi.jpg
